More than 20 million hectares of forest have been brought under protection and 3.61 million hectares of forest have been planted  since 1997.
The latest national  survey on giant panda, which was organized by the State Forestry  Administration, showed that the population and habitat of the  pandas in Sichuan have both increased 30 percent during the past  seven years.
The central and provincial governments have invested 160  million yuan (nearly 20 million US dollars) into panda protection  programs since 1992.
The nature preserve, occupying about 220,000 hectares, has 102  giant pandas living wild.
But in Sichuan and in Shaanxi province, which also has panda  reserves, arrow bamboo has also been found blooming.
